Defendant Tyrell J Steward in court with Attorney Angele R. Dentice.  
Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Matter before the Court for Sentencing.  Hearing proceeded.  Statements made by the state, defense, and defendant.

COUNT 1:  The Court ordered the defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction STRAIGHT TIME.

The Court IMPOSED AND STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 18 MONTHS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens;
*No firearms;
*No gang involvement;
*Perform 30 hours of community service;
*Obtain full time employment OR attend school full time OR combination of the two;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment- apply bail;

The Court ordered restitution set at zero.  The Court grants expungement of this matter ONLY if defendant successfully completion of ALL probation conditions ordered by the court.

